            "title": "Convert Date Format",
            "titleSlug": "convert-date-format",
            "content": "<p>Table: <code>Days</code></p>\n\n<pre>\n+-------------+------+\n| Column Name | Type |\n+-------------+------+\n| day         | date |\n+-------------+------+\nday is the primary key for this table.\n</pre>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Write an SQL query to convert each date in <code>Days</code> into a string formatted as <code>&quot;day_name, month_name day, year&quot;</code>.</p>\n\n<p>Return the result table <strong>in any order</strong>.</p>\n\n<p>The query result format is in the following example:</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<pre>\nDays table:\n+------------+\n| day        |\n+------------+\n| 2022-04-12 |\n| 2021-08-09 |\n| 2020-06-26 |\n+------------+\n\nResult table:\n+-------------------------+\n| day                     |\n+-------------------------+\n| Tuesday, April 12, 2022 |\n| Monday, August 9, 2021  |\n| Friday, June 26, 2020   |\n+-------------------------+\nPlease note that the output is case-sensitive.\n</pre>\n",
